# Dashboard UX Patterns

## Responsive Tables

- **Always use table layout** — never duplicate as mobile card view
- Wrap tables in `overflow-x-auto` for horizontal scroll on small screens
- Add `whitespace-nowrap` to key cells to prevent line breaks
- First identifying column: `sticky left-0 z-[1] bg-base-100` to stay visible during horizontal scroll
- `<thead>` must be sticky: `sticky top-0 z-10 bg-base-100`

```html
<!-- ✅ GOOD -->
<div class="overflow-x-auto">
  <table class="table table-zebra">
    <thead class="sticky top-0 z-10 bg-base-100">…</thead>
    <tbody>…</tbody>
  </table>
</div>

<!-- ❌ BAD — separate mobile card view -->
<div class="hidden lg:block"><!-- table --></div>
<div class="lg:hidden"><!-- cards --></div>
```

## Sortable Column Headers

- Clickable `<th>` toggles ASC → DESC → none
- Show arrow indicators (▲/▼/neutral) next to sorted column
- Always validate sortable columns against a backend whitelist
- Add `cursor-pointer select-none` to sortable `<th>`

## Filter Layout

- Use `flex flex-wrap gap-*` for filters — not rigid grid
- Search input is prominent (wider, primary visual weight)
- Group: search + dropdowns + toggles + clear button in one wrapping row
- Active filters displayed as dismissible badges/chips above the table
- "Netejar filtres" button always visible when any filter is active

## Collapsible Secondary Controls

- Wrap non-essential controls (column visibility, display options) in DaisyUI `collapse` — closed by default
- Show a summary count in the collapse title: `"Columnes visibles (8 de 12)"`

```html
<div class="collapse collapse-arrow bg-base-200/50 rounded-lg">
  <input type="checkbox" />
  <div class="collapse-title text-sm font-medium py-2 min-h-0">
    Columnes visibles ({{ visibleCount() }} de {{ totalCount }})
  </div>
  <div class="collapse-content">…</div>
</div>
```

## Visual Hierarchy

- Record count badge next to page title: `"Persones (143)"`
- Table rows: `hover cursor-pointer transition-colors` for clickable rows
- Color-coded values when semantically meaningful (green = positive, red = negative)

## Pagination

- Include a per-page selector (25 / 50 / 100) — never hardcode page size
- Show range info near controls: `"Mostrant X – Y de Z"`
- Disable prev/next at boundaries

## Loading & Empty States

- Use skeleton loaders (`bg-base-300 animate-pulse rounded`) instead of spinners
- Provide meaningful empty state messages (Catalan) with suggested actions

```html
<!-- ✅ Skeleton row -->
<tr>
  <td><div class="h-4 w-24 bg-base-300 animate-pulse rounded"></div></td>
  <td><div class="h-4 w-32 bg-base-300 animate-pulse rounded"></div></td>
</tr>

<!-- ❌ Just a spinner -->
<div class="flex justify-center"><span class="loading loading-spinner"></span></div>
```

## Accessibility Baseline

- All interactive elements must be keyboard-navigable
- Toggle inputs use `<label class="label cursor-pointer gap-2">` wrapping
- Table headers use `scope="col"`, row headers use `scope="row"`
- Buttons and toggles include descriptive text (no icon-only without `aria-label`)
